Application.Controller

Class FeelingController

  • java.lang.Object
    • Application.Controller.FeelingController

  • @SessionAttributes(value="scenarioId")
 @Controller
public class FeelingController
extends java.lang.Object
    Controller class for managing the page in which the User(s) express their Feeling(s). The page contains the model with all the feeling among which the User(s) can choose.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Corti Lorenzo, Tocchetti Andrea

    • Method Detail

      • getFeelings

        @RequestMapping(value="/feelings",
                method={GET,POST})
public java.lang.String getFeelings(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                                                                                          @RequestParam(value="scenarioId",required=false,defaultValue="0")
                                                                                                          java.lang.Integer scenarioId,
                                                                                                          @CookieValue(value="user_id",defaultValue="NULL")
                                                                                                          java.lang.String user_id,
                                                                                                          @SessionAttribute(value="referral",required=false)
                                                                                                          java.lang.String referral,
                                                                                                          @RequestParam(name="lang",defaultValue="en")
                                                                                                          java.lang.String lang,
                                                                                                          javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request)
        Returns the page containing the model through which the User(s) can express their Feeling(s). User(s) share their Feeling(s) twice. Once when the User first join the Scenario. The second time when they have played a specific amount of Match(es).
        Parameters:
        model - Spring Model object.
        scenarioId - The unique identifier of the Scenario.
        user_id - The unique identifier of the User.
        referral - The referral code of the User.
        lang - The language chosen by the User.
        request - Instance of HttpServletRequest class.
        Returns:
        "feelings" string indicating the name of the Thymeleaf template to parse and return to the client.

      • submitFeels

        @RequestMapping(value="/saveFeelings",
                method=POST)
public java.lang.String submitFeels(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                                                                                        @ModelAttribute(value="scenarioId")
                                                                                                        java.lang.Integer scenarioId,
                                                                                                        @CookieValue(value="user_id",defaultValue="NULL")
                                                                                                        java.lang.String user_id,
                                                                                                        @RequestParam(value="feelingsVote")
                                                                                                        int vote,
                                                                                                        @RequestParam(value="opinion")
                                                                                                        java.lang.String opinion)
        Saves the Feeling(s) expressed by the User(s).
        Parameters:
        model - Spring Model object.
        scenarioId - The unique identifier of the Scenario.
        user_id - The unique identifier of the User.
        vote - The numerical representation of the Feeling shared by the User.
        opinion - The opinion about the Feeling shared by the User.
        Returns:
        A string indicating the name of the Thymeleaf template to parse and return to the client. Possible returned strings (depending on whether the User expressed their Feeling(s) once or twice) are:
        • "redirect:/feed"
        • "redirect:/error"
        • "redirect:/vision"
